.txbox_blue {
  border: 1px solid black;
  color: white;
  box-shadow: 1px 2px 2px black;
  font-weight: 900;
  padding-right: 5px;
  padding-left: 5px;
  border-radius: 20px;
  display: inline-block;
  background-color: #2a4e8a;
  position: center;
}

.txbox_green {
  border: 1px solid black;
  color: white;
  box-shadow: 1px 2px 2px black;
  font-weight: 900;
  padding-right: 5px;
  padding-left: 5px;
  border-radius: 20px;
  display: inline-block;
  background-color: #3dbc8b; 
  position: center;
}


/* styling text circles and centered image with drop shadow */
.numberCircle {
    display:inline-block;
    border-radius:50%;
    font-family: Calibri,Candara,Segoe,Segoe UI,Optima,Arial,sans-serif;
    font-size:22.5px;
    font-weight: bold;
    color: white;
    /* line-height:22.5px; */
    text-align:center;
    background:#3399ff;
}

.numberCircle:before,
.numberCircle:after {
    content:'\200B';
    display:inline-block;
    line-height:0px;
    padding-top:50%;
    padding-bottom:50%;
}

.numberCircle:before {
    padding-left:4px;
}
.numberCircle:after {
    padding-right:4px;
}

.bordered{
  box-shadow: 0 4px 8px 0 rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
  margin: auto;
  text-align: center;
  display: block;
  width: 75%;
  transition: transform .5s; /* Animation */
}


.bordered:hover {
    transform: scale(1.5); 
    transition-delay: 1.5s;
}

#parent {
    list-style: none;
    width: 100%;
    height: 90px;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    white-space: nowrap;
    overflow-x: auto;
    overflow-y: hidden;
}

#parent > li {
    display: inline-block;
    width: 50%;
    height: 100%;
    background-color: red;
}</style>
<!-- #  <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #2a4e8a; !important;">Quick Start</span> #conflicts with bookdown-->
<p><img style="width:50% !important;" class="bordered" src="data:image/png;base64,"></p>
<div id="dave-is-comprised-of-individual-modules-which-can-be-linked-to-create-a-variety-of-unique-data-analysis-workflows.-the-global-utilities-include-data-and-report-and-provide-an-overview-of-objects-shared-by-the-data-analysis-tools.-the-majority-of-analyses-start-with-data-upload-using-the-data-module-and-then-preparation-using-preprocess.-check-out-the-analysis-workflows-section-for-more-examles." class="section level4">
<h4>DAVe is comprised of individual <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3dbc8b !important;">modules</span> which can be linked to create a variety of unique data analysis workflows. The <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #2a4e8a; !important;">Global Utilities</span> include <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3dbc8b !important;">Data</span> and <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3dbc8b !important;">Report</span> and provide an overview of objects shared by the <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #2a4e8a; !important;">Data Analysis Tools</span>. The majority of analyses start with data upload using the <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3dbc8b !important;">Data</span> module and then preparation using <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3dbc8b !important;">Preprocess</span>. Check out the <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #2a4e8a; !important;">Analysis Workflows</span> section for more examles.</h4>
<p><img class="bordered" src="data:image/png;base64,"></p>
<p><br></p>
<div class="numberCircle">
A
</div>
<div class="txbox_blue">
<h3>
Select Modules
</h3>
</div>
<br>
<h4>
The navigation bar is used to select different analyses. Each analysis may also have sub-options. Typical workflows will include choosing modules from the nav bar progressing from left to right and while optimizing each step with sub analyses by progressing through each modules method controls from top to bottom. See the <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #2a4e8a; !important;">Analysis Workflows</span> section for details how to save and propogate results between induvidual modules.
</h4>
<p><br></p>
<div class="numberCircle">
B
</div>
<div class="txbox_blue">
<h3>
Module Controls
</h3>
</div>
<br>
<h4>
The sidebar is used to select analyses methods, tune visualizations and specify report options.
</h4>
<p><br></p>
<div class="numberCircle">
C
</div>
<div class="txbox_blue">
<h3>
Progress Analyses
</h3>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<h4>
The tabpanel can be used to switch between calculation, interactive exploration, static plotting and report generation. Use <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3399ff !important;">calculate</span> to select method options and generate data objects. <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3399ff !important;">Explore</span> provides interactive visualizations, while <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3399ff !important;">plot</span> is used to tune how the visualizations will appear in the <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3399ff !important;">report</span>. The <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3399ff !important;">report</span> tab is used to collect all methods, results and plot settings and generate a report of methods and results. The <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3399ff !important;">report</span> may also include additional information not present in the previous tabs and can be dynamically populated based on user selected visualizations. All analyses report results can be combined and further manipulated in navbar <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3dbc8b !important;">Report</span> module.
</h4>
<p><br></p>
<div class="numberCircle">
D
</div>
<div class="txbox_blue">
<h3>
Results and Methods
</h3>
</div>
<br>
<h4>
This is the main panel where calculation, exploration, plotting and report results will be output to. Results may include both static and interactive results which can be manipulated further.
</h4>
<p><br></p>
<div class="numberCircle">
E
</div>
<div class="txbox_blue">
<h3>
Help
</h3>
</div>
<br>
<h4>
Select this icon to to view the help menu for each selected analyses.
</h4>
</div>
<!--/html_preserve-->

<!-- ## <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #2a4e8a; !important;">Analysis Workflows</span> -->
<p><img style="width: 50% !important;" class="bordered" src="data:image/png;base64,"></p>
<p><br></p>
<div id="each-module-shares-internal-workflow-elements.-the-analyses-proceed-using-the-calculate-tab-to-set-the-methods-and-get-results." class="section level4">
<h4>Each module shares internal workflow elements. The analyses proceed using the <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3399ff !important;">calculate</span> tab to set the methods and get results.</h4>
<p><img style="width: 50% !important;" class="bordered" src="data:image/png;base64,"></p>
</div>
<div id="the-results-can-be-visualized-using-static-plot-or-interactive-explore-tabs.-the-methods-results-and-created-visualizations-can-be-summarized-in-the-report.-this-can-be-done-iteratively-to-explore-and-refine-the-analysis-results-and-summaries.-once-the-results-reached-the-data-object-can-be-saved-using-the-controls-at-the-bottom-of-the-calculate-menu." class="section level4">
<h4>The results can be visualized using static <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3399ff !important;">plot</span> or interactive <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3399ff !important;">explore</span> tabs. The methods, results and created visualizations can be summarized in the <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3399ff !important;">report</span>. This can be done iteratively to explore and refine the analysis results and summaries. Once the results reached the data object can be <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3399ff !important;">saved</span> using the controls at the bottom of the <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3399ff !important;">calculate</span> menu.</h4>
<div class="numberCircle">
1
</div>
<div class="txbox_blue">
<h3>
Upload Data
</h3>
</div>
<br> <br>
<h4>
Load data from a <code>.csv</code> or saved project.
</h4>
<div class="numberCircle">
2
</div>
<div class="txbox_blue">
<h3>
Prepare Data
</h3>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<p><img style="width: 50% !important;" class="bordered" src="data:image/png;base64,"></p>
<br>
<h4>
Use the <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3dbc8b !important;">Preprocess</span> module to specify sample meta data and merge with variable information. Review and impute missing values.
</h4>
<div class="numberCircle">
3
</div>
<div class="txbox_blue">
<h3>
Save Results
</h3>
</div>
<br> <br>
<h4>
Each modules calculations and results can be saved and used in further analyses. The <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3399ff !important;">save</span> controls found at the bottom of each module&#39;s controls menu can be used to specify various parameters to add to the global data sets.
</h4>
<div class="numberCircle">
4
</div>
<div class="txbox_blue">
<h3>
Generate Reports
</h3>
</div>
<p><img style="width: 50% !important;" class="bordered" src="data:image/png;base64,"></p>
<h4>
Each modules results, methods and visualizations can be saved to the analysis <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3399ff !important;">report</span>. Individual module&#39;s reports can be combined and further modified using the global <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3dbc8b !important;">report</span> module.
</h4>
<div class="numberCircle">
5
</div>
<div class="txbox_blue">
<h3>
Statistical Analysis
</h3>
</div>
<br> <br> <img style="width: 50% !important;" class="bordered" src="data:image/png;base64,">
<h4>
The <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3dbc8b !important;">statistics</span> module can be used to compare changes in variables among groups of samples and calculate summary statistics.
</h4>
<div class="numberCircle">
6
</div>
<div class="txbox_blue">
<h3>
Pathway Analysis
</h3>
</div>
<br> <br> <img style="width: 50% !important;" class="bordered" src="data:image/png;base64,">
<h4>
The p-values and fold changes calculated <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3dbc8b !important;">statistics</span> module can be used to calculate pathway enrichment. The enriched pathways can be visualized to show the direction of significant changes in variables mapped to biochemical pathways.
</h4>
<div class="numberCircle">
7
</div>
<div class="txbox_blue">
<h3>
Clustering
</h3>
</div>
<br> <br> <img style="width: 50% !important;" class="bordered" src="data:image/png;base64,">
<h4>
Use the <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3dbc8b !important;">cluster</span> module to identify groups of related samples or variables. Use <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3dbc8b !important;">Hierarchical Clustering (HCA)</span> on the full data or sample and variable correlation. Visualize meta data and cluster relationships with heatmaps and dendrograms.
</h4>
<div class="numberCircle">
8
</div>
<div class="txbox_blue">
<h3>
Dimensional Reduction
</h3>
</div>
<br> <br> <img style="width: 50% !important;" class="bordered" src="data:image/png;base64,">
<h4>
Use the <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3dbc8b !important;">multivariate</span> module to calculate lower dimensional summaries of multivariate data. Use <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3dbc8b !important;">Principal Components Analysis (PCA)</span> to visualize the major modes of variance in samples, variables and their correlations.
</h4>
<div class="numberCircle">
9
</div>
<div class="txbox_blue">
<h3>
Predictive Modeling
</h3>
</div>
<br> <br> <img style="width: 50% !important;" class="bordered" src="data:image/png;base64,">
<h4>
Use the <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3dbc8b !important;">model</span> module to calculate <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3dbc8b !important;">machine learning (ML)</span> models to identify predictive relationships for groups or continuous variables. Use auto ML to optimize and tune models while choosing from over 200 available algorithms. Carry out feature selection to rank important variables for explaining the model performance.
</h4>
<div class="numberCircle">
10
</div>
<div class="txbox_blue">
<h3>
Network Analysis and Mapping
</h3>
</div>
<br> <br> <img style="width: 50% !important;" class="bordered" src="data:image/png;base64,">
<h4>
Use the <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3dbc8b !important;">network</span> module to identify <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3dbc8b !important;">biochemical</span>, <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3dbc8b !important;">structural similarity</span> and <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3dbc8b !important;">regularized correlation</span> relationships between variables.
</h4>
<p><img style="width: 50% !important;" class="bordered" src="data:image/png;base64,"></p>
<h4>
Use the <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3dbc8b !important;">network</span> module to combine the results from other modules by using <span class="txbox_green" style="background-color: #3dbc8b !important;">network mapping</span> to visualize meta data, statistical, clustering, dimensional reduction, predictive modeling and pathway analysis results. Use highly interactive network visualizations to fine tune publication quality static graphics.
</h4>
</div>
